== Brussels Sprouts and Couscous ==

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry
all produce. Trim and halve @Brussels Sprouts{8%ounce} lengthwise. Trim and
thinly slice @Button Mushrooms{4%ounce}. Peel and mince or grate @Garlic{1%clove}.

Toss Brussels sprouts on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @oil{drizzle},
@salt{pinch}, and @pepper{}; arrange cut sides down. Roast on top rack until
browned and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}. Meanwhile, melt @Butter{1%tbsp}(plain)
in a #medium pot{} over medium-high heat. Add @Israeli Couscous{1/2%cup}
and cook until toasted, ~{1-2%minutes}. Stir in @water{3/4%cup} and a big
pinch of @salt{pinch}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce heat to low.
Cook until couscous is tender, ~{6-8%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until
ready to serve.

== Beef and Sauce ==

While couscous cooks, pat @Beef Tenderloin Filets{10%ounce} dry with
#paper towels{}; season all over with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Heat a large
drizzle of @vegetable oil{4%tsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat.
Add beef and cook to desired doneness, ~{4-7%minutes} per side. Remove from
pan and set aside to rest.

Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{} in same pan over medium-high heat. Add
mushrooms and cook, stirring, until softened and lightly browned,
~{3-4%minutes}. Add garlic and cook until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Stir @Beef Demi-Glace{1} and @water{1/4%cup} into pan with mushroom mixture,
scraping up any browned bits from bottom of pan. Bring to a simmer, then
reduce heat to medium and cook until thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}. Turn off
heat; stir in @Sour Cream{2%tbsp} and @Butter{1%tbsp}(plain) until melted.
Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

== To Serve ==

Fluff couscous with a #fork{}; stir in @Garlic Herb Butter{2%tbsp} and season
with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Divide Brussels sprouts, couscous, and beef
between plates. Top beef with sauce and serve.

